# Align with `docs/AGENTS.md`

For every code change in repo (new code, refactor, tests, wiring), follow `docs/AGENTS.md`.
Goal: keep product words, package boundaries, repo conventions aligned.

Before big edits, skim/re-read `docs/AGENTS.md` (and deeper refs it points to). Treat as source of truth for:

- Terminology: bridge vs relay vs process, `from` / `to`, relay orchestration in `pkg/bifrost`, avoid names like `bridgeRuntime`.
- Layout/responsibility: where `cmd/bifrost`, `pkg/bifrost`, `pkg/bridge`, `pkg/config`, `pkg/kafka`, `pkg/metrics`, tests belong (`test/unit/<package>/` for `pkg/*`).
- Naming/imports: do not shadow `pkg/bridge` import with local `bridge`; keep action-oriented names in `pkg/bifrost`.
- Errors/metrics: error wrapping style, metric prefixes `bifrost_` and `bifrost_relay_*`.
- Anti-patterns: no catch-all `util` / `helpers`; test behavior changes in `pkg/` and relay wiring.

If generic advice conflicts with `docs/AGENTS.md`, pick `docs/AGENTS.md`.
If public behavior or big package boundaries change, update `docs/AGENTS.md` in same effort.
